{ Bringing out the queen, and protecting the bishop at the same time. } 14. Nc7
Ne4
{ Powerful play! A little reminder to White that they aren't the only ones creating threats here. }
15. Rxc5 { The most responsible decision, given the circumstances. } 15... Nxc5
16. Nxa8 Rxa8
{ At the end of this tactical sequence, the smoke has cleared and an approximately equal position has emerged. }
17. Be3 { A clever way of addressing the threat of ...Qxb2. } 17... Qb5
{ Getting out of the pin is simple and sound. Black faces no problems. If White allows it, our knight from c5 can jump to the beautiful b3-square. }
