{ As in the 10.Bg5 line, both  13.Nd5  and  13.Ne4  are playable for White. }
13. Nd5 Qd8 14. Nd2
{ This shouldn't be worrying to us as the plan of tucking away our bishop is available here as well. }
14... Re8 15. Rc1 Bf8
{ With the two bishops well preserved, our position is good. If anything, the pawn on a5 is slightly advantageous to us, as the computer starts pointing out ideas such as ...a5-a4, gaining some more space on the queenside. }
