11... Ne4 { Seems like a good start, already vacating the f6-square. } 12. Bb2
Re8
{ We shouldn't rush with ...Bf6 but can maximally improve our pieces instead. }
13. Rc1 h5
{ A typical idea for this line, and another hidden point behind 11...Ne4, as our bishop is also controlling the h4-square from e7, sustaining the march of the h-pawn. }
