{ I quite like this move, which should by now be second nature to many players, mainly due to the influence of neural network engines. If allowed the pawn may advance all the way to h3, where it will be quite the nuisance for White. At the same time, any attempts to stop the pawn from reaching there will weaken the white kingside. }
17. Qd2 { A sneaky move - we must react accurately. } 17... Qd6
{ A good reply, as White was intending to play 18.Qf4. Now, we have a comfortable game ahead of us. We can bring our rook to d8, as well as keep pushing the h-pawn down the board. }
