15. Re1
{ This move has been tried twice by Dutch player Loek van Wely in his games against Alexander Grischuk. A subtle improving move, overprotecting the pawn on e2 and freeing up the queen.  However, generally, when playing against the bishop pair, slow playing the position works in favour of the bishops as they will sooner or later be stronger than the knights. Therefore, we should not be worried when seeing moves like these and we can happily continue making our favourite moves. }
15... Bf5
{ Out of the three logical bishop moves I like this one best, the point being that  16.Nb3  is now well met by  16...Be4  .  Therefore it is once again up to White to find a new plan. We, on the other hand, can easily improve our position with moves like ...Rc8. }
