{ The most popular move, played by Jovanka Houska among others.   In his excellent course on the Catalan, Srinath Narayanan recommends starting with  15.Nxb6  , which although possible is a slightly strange move order since it allows the additional option of  15...Nxf1  .   Regardless, we can still play @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/pp4pp/1Nn1b3/5p2/3p4/P5P1/1P1nPPBP/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 0 15@@EndFEN@@  15...axb6  when  16.Bxd2  O-O  transposes to the 15.Bxd2 move order. }
15... O-O
{ Having brought our king to safety, we can set about to exchange bishops through ...Bd5. The pawn on d4 is much more of a strength than a weakness, as it restricts the c1-bishop quite a bit. }
