{ Srinath ends his variation here, claiming a slight advantage for White since they have the better pawn structure. I beg to differ, as I feel our space advantage, and control over the light squares compensates for the structural deficit. }
20... Qf7
{ We should keep the queens on the board for activity.  A strong plan would be to occupy the e-file and potentially bring a rook to the juicy e4-square. Once the rook has established itself there, the queen can return to d5 as well. Due to our excellent central control, and the soft e2-pawn, White will not be in time to exploit the weak doubled b-pawns.  Another useful move to include is ...h6 at times, creating some air for the king, just in case. }
