[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "5) Fianchetto w/o Nc3 – 8.dxc5 Bxc5 – Other 9th Moves"]
[Black "Fianchetto Without Nc3 – 8.dxc5 Bxc5 9.Nbd2"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5
{ This is the starting position of the Tarrasch Defense. } 4. cxd5 exd5 5. g3
{ The fianchetto variation has always stood out as the critical method of combating the Tarrasch. The main reason is that from g2, the bishop will be able to exert great pressure on d5. In addition, the castled king will be highly secure. }
5... Nf6
{ Playing ...Nf6 before ...Nc6 is important. This idea has only recently become known and is quickly gaining in popularity, avoiding dull and tedious endgames and spicing stuff up. }
6. Bg2 Nc6 7. O-O Be7 8. dxc5
{ White releases the tension as soon as we have played ...Be7, forcing us to spend another tempo recapturing. Moreover, it should be noted that White has delayed the development of the b1-knight. By doing so, White gets access to a couple of new setups that need to be investigated. }
8... Bxc5 9. Nbd2
{ Almost 200 players have opted for this move, intending to play the knight to d4. However, besides being a slow plan, it is also just not good. All the critical plans for White revolve around attacking the isolated pawn, not blockading it.   9.Nc3  is a direct transposition to the chapter Fianchetto with Nc3 – 9.dxc5 Bxc5. }
9... O-O 10. Nb3 Bb6 { Keeping the bishop active. } 11. Nbd4
{ Once again, the most played move, but the computer already assigns a serious advantage to Black by this point. In most cases, two knights defending each other are not good. It was Dvoretsky who came up with the term 'superfluous knights', which is exactly the case here. The knights are only standing in each other's way and are rather vulnerable. }
11... Re8 { All of the routine moves are simple and good for us. } 12. b3 Ne4
13. Bb2 Bg4
{ The white position is already under some serious pressure, and they need to be extremely careful not to collapse immediately. Regardless, it is clear that the opening has been a great success for Black. }
*

