[Black "Fianchetto Without Nc3 – 8.dxc5 Bxc5 9.Bg5"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5
{ This is the starting position of the Tarrasch Defense. } 4. cxd5 exd5 5. g3
{ The fianchetto variation has always stood out as the critical method of combating the Tarrasch. The main reason is that from g2, the bishop will be able to exert great pressure on d5. In addition, the castled king will be highly secure. }
5... Nf6
{ Playing ...Nf6 before ...Nc6 is important. This idea has only recently become known and is quickly gaining in popularity, avoiding dull and tedious endgames and spicing stuff up. }
6. Bg2 Nc6 7. O-O Be7 8. dxc5
{ White releases the tension as soon as we have played ...Be7, forcing us to spend another tempo recapturing. Moreover, it should be noted that White has delayed the development of the b1-knight. By doing so, White gets access to a couple of new setups that need to be investigated. }
8... Bxc5 9. Bg5
{ It is possible to start with this move, but the likelihood of play soon transposing to variations we are familiar with is high.   9.Nc3  is a direct transposition to the chapter Fianchetto with Nc3 – 9.dxc5 Bxc5. }
9... O-O 10. Qc1 { An interesting way to try and confuse us. } 10... Be7
{ In the Qc2 lines, we could keep the bishop on the active diagonal due to some ...Bf5 tactics down the line. With the queen on c1, however, these tactics do not work and we should retreat the bishop back the other way. }
11. Nc3 Be6
{ It is easy to be tempted by  11...d4  , but  12.Rd1!  is a venomous reply. Therefore, it is better to keep the pawn on d5 for the moment. }
12. Rd1 h6 13. Bxf6 Bxf6 14. e4
{ An exciting move to make, but it will quickly dry up the board. In any case, with the bishop pair, we should be doing fine after alternative moves as well. }
14... d4 { Forcing matters. } 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. exd5 Qxd5 17. Nxd4 Nxd4
{ Other moves are possible, but this is the most effective way of killing the game. }
18. Bxd5 Ne2+ 19. Kg2 Nxc1 20. Raxc1 Rac8
{ Lots of trades later we have reached a dead-drawn endgame. } *

