7. Qb3 { A crafty queen sortie, attacking both d5 and b7. } 7... Nc6
{ We should not be faced, by these minor threats as developing the knight priority number one. }
8. Qxb7
{ While growing up in the Dutch school of chess, if we could say there is such - we learn the rule of never capture on b2, even if it is good. The same applies here. }
8... Nb4
{ Blocking the way back for the queen, as well as introducing the threat of ... Nc2+. }
9. Rc1 Rb8 { A typical idea, attacking the queen to eternity leads to a draw. }
10. Qxa7 Ra8 11. Qb7 Rb8 { With a repetition of moves. } *

