[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5
{ This is the starting position of the Tarrasch Defense. } 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5
{ A vicious variation that should be studied carefully. As I have not been able to find a name for this variation yet, I will call it the Korchnoi Variation. He was one of the first players to employ it regularly at a high level. }
