{ Now  6.Nf3  Nc6  transposes to 3.Nf3 c5 4.e3 Nf6 5.Nc3 Nc6 6.cxd5 #1 and  @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pp3ppp/5n2/2pp4/3P4/2N1P3/PP3PPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Bb5+  Nc6  7.Nf3  transposes to 3.Nf3 c5 4.e3 Nf6 5.Nc3 Nc6 6.cxd5 #5 - both covered later in this chapter.   Both variations are normally reached through the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  c5  4.e3  move order. }
