{ The most accurate way.   Most people have played  7...Bd6  instead, but after  8.dxc5  we must move our bishop again.   I recently played  7...a6  in an online rapid game vs Ding Liren, but after  8.Bxc6+  I soon found myself in  trouble. }
8. exd4
{ By appearances this recapture looks rather harmless. However, don't be deceived as White's small lead in development requires us to react accurately in order not to land in a difficult situation. }
8... Bd6 9. O-O O-O 10. h3
{ This has been played by some strong players, but I struggle to see the danger.   Instead,  10.Bg5  would  transpose to the 9.Bg5 line. }
10... h6
{ There is no need to do anything special, just stopping ...Bg5 will serve us just fine. We'll develop next with ...Bf5.  A model game from Black's side was recently seen in the online game Carlsen-Praggnanandhaa, where the young Indian managed to defeat the World Champion! }
