Nbd2
{ Bringing the knight out is probably the most critical, but as we already know ...g7-g5 is a threat that will be constantly looming. }
11... a5
{ A typical idea, stopping White from making any advances on the Queenside with a2-a3 followed by b2-b4.   Instead,  11...g5  would not have won a piece yet due to  12.Be5  , escaping. However, we keep this idea in our pocket as we may well be able to use it at a later stage. }
12. a3 Be7
{ Retreating with the bishop is best, as it is safe and sound here.   Note that  12...Bc5  would be less accurate here due to  13.Ne4  , hitting the bishop.  We simply plan to castle next, and see how White proceeds. }
13. g4
{ This move was played in the game Sjugirov-Iljushenkok, 2021. It is a weakening move, but Sjugirov was evidently worried about losing the bishop to ...g7-g5. }
13... O-O 14. Rb1 a4
{ Another typical idea, so that b2-b4 can be captured en passant. Black is already slightly better and can try to play in various ways, such as ...Nc5, or even develop the rook along the sixth rank with ...Ra6. }
