1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 c5
{ This is the starting position of the Tarrasch Defense. } 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Nc3
Nf6 6. g3 Nc6 7. Bg2 Be7
{ Now, although White has some alternatives to going  8.O-O  here, most of them will transpose to the other chapters later on since White can't delay castling forever. }
8. Be3
{ The most noteworthy thing about this move is that Korchnoi played it against Carlsen and later on, Carlsen also played it himself, but there is not much to be worried about.  Sooner or later White has to castle, taking us to the Fianchetto With Nc3 – 9.dxc5 chapter. }
8... c4 9. O-O O-O
{ Transposing to the 8.Be3 move in the Fianchetto With Nc3 – Other 9th Moves chapter. }
